Explanation:
We iterate through the digits of the number using a while loop, adding each digit to the sum variable. Since we only need to consider the digits, we divide the number by 10 in each iteration to remove the last digit. The time complexity is O(log(n)) because we only iterate until the number becomes 0. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the sum variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm is efficient and requires minimal resources.

